  "title": "SearchBox widget does not change its state after calling helpers.setState",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n`search.helper.setState({query: undefined});` does not clear the SearchBox widget state.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://jsfiddle.net/7d9zr0ja/3/\r\n2. Click on \"Open search popup\"\r\n3. Type a text to the input field\r\n4. Click on \"Close\"\r\n5. Open the popup again - you can see that input has a value.\r\n\r\n**Live reproduction:**\r\n\r\nhttps://jsfiddle.net/7d9zr0ja/3/\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThere is an API method that allow to clear SearchBox widget state programmatically.\r\n\r\n## Additional context\r\nHi there!\r\nI expected that `search.helper.setState` would change state for SearchBox too, but it did not happen. Maybe there is another way to achieve this? I tried to find one, but nothing worked.\r\nThank you!",
